ASSESSMENT: WHERE THE PROJECT STANDS TODAY
After a thorough review of every file, folder, and code artifact in this repository, here is the honest state of the project:

What EXISTS and is functional (backend scaffolding):

8 backend microservices scaffolded (incident, commitment, traffic, emergency, identity, notification, ai-agent, citizen-vault) -- each with Fastify/Python entry points, health checks, and Dockerfiles
Docker Compose orchestrating PostgreSQL/PostGIS, Redis, Mosquitto, MongoDB, MinIO, NGINX/OpenResty, and all services
7 SQL migration files covering BARAZA tables, agency directory, scorecards, contextual promotions, and civic insights
Shared TypeScript constants (MQTT topics, service ports, commitment FSM, sync priority, incident categories, SLA defaults)
NGINX gateway routing all /api/v1/* paths to services
Mosquitto ACL configuration with topic-level permissions
MongoDB time-series collection initialization
CI/CD pipeline (GitHub Actions) with lint, test, build, and compose smoke test
CodeQL security scanning and Dependabot configuration
Comprehensive architectural documentation (4 foundational docs totaling ~30,000 words)
What is MISSING or BROKEN (critical gaps):

No init.sql file -- The docker-compose.yml references ./postgres/init.sql but this file does not exist. The 7 migration files in infra/postgres/migrations/ are never executed by Docker. The core tables (citizens, wards, incidents) defined in the Master Prompt schema have NO migration files at all. The database will start empty.

No Android build system -- There are zero Gradle files (build.gradle.kts, settings.gradle.kts), no AndroidManifest.xml, no dependency declarations. The 6 Kotlin files in android/ are orphaned source files that cannot compile. There is no Room database, no Hilt DI, no Ktor client, no MapLibre integration, no WorkManager, no navigation graph.

No tests -- Every service's package.json has "test": "echo \"No tests yet\" && exit 0". Zero actual test coverage.

No input validation -- Every route handler uses request.body as any with no Fastify JSON schema validation. This violates the .cursorrules requirement for complete type definitions.

No MQTT integration in services -- The incident service, commitment service, and identity service have no MQTT publish logic despite the architecture requiring it. The emergency service references fastify.mqtt but the MQTT plugin is only in the traffic and notification services.

No Supabase database -- The connected Supabase instance has zero tables, zero migrations, and PostGIS is not enabled. The entire data layer is Docker-only.

No data/ directory -- The monorepo layout specifies wards.geojson, agencies.json, routing-rules.json, and sla-defaults.json -- none of these exist.

Color system mismatch -- The Android theme uses "Neon Green on Black" (#39FF14) which contradicts the Master Prompt's specification of "Kenyan earth tones: deep green (#1B5E20) primary, warm amber (#FF8F00) accent, red (#D32F2F) for emergencies."

UI prototypes are React Native, not Jetpack Compose -- The shared/ui-prototypes/ files use React Native imports, not Kotlin Compose. These are reference mockups, not usable code.

HomeScreen has a compile error -- DeviceTierManager.getTier() is called as a static method but the class requires a Context constructor parameter.

